The paper discusses monitoring techniques in the context of software systems and their impact on user experience. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the storage and computational resources required for monitoring, which could fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions measuring overhead, which could be related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The fact that the monitoring is done in the field suggests that the paper could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses designing monitoring solutions, which could be related to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
